# Create this in the Appwrite console: Project Settings -> API Keys -> Create API Key
# Scopes needed: databases.read + documents.read (read-only, no write scopes)
# (console may label the second one "Documents" or "Rows" depending on version)
# NOTE: deliberately NOT prefixed with APPWRITE_ or made NEXT_PUBLIC_ — reads now
# happen server-side with a privileged key, not from the browser. The APPWRITE_
# prefix is also reserved by Appwrite Sites itself, which silently overrides
# custom vars of that name.
CMS_API_KEY=
